 {"id":"bd-qij6l","title":"printf %n disabled by FORTIFY but fixture expects it to work","description":"Modern glibc disables %n in snprintf for security (FORTIFY_SOURCE). Our impl honors it. Fixture sprintf_n_count_mid in printf_conformance.json expects the cross-impl comparison to succeed, but host glibc refuses %n so host_output is empty while our impl emits 'hello'. Either the fixture should be removed/hardened-only, or the comparison should tolerate the host's security-hardening difference.","notes":"Closed by cc-libc. Fix landed as two parts: (1) no-arg %n cases (sprintf_n_count_zero, sprintf_n_count_mid) re-tagged mode=hardened in tests/conformance/fixtures/printf_conformance.json — now run against impl only, no host parity needed under FORTIFY. (2) executor DSL gap for sprintf_n_with_args (requires int* output arg) split off as bd-c5aak. Validation: cargo test -p frankenlibc-harness --test printf_conformance_conformance_test -> 14 passed; 174 fixtures executed; 13 skipped (only sprintf_n_with_args for bd-c5aak, rest unrelated bd-luc3d et al.).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-libc","created_at":"2026-04-22T05:34:31.156927535Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:40:18.798686126Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T10:40:18.796205224Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-qjl2a","title":"syscall: renameat2 exchange with null newpath should return EFAULT exactly","description":"Host glibc returns EFAULT for renameat2(AT_FDCWD, \".\", AT_FDCWD, NULL, RENAME_EXCHANGE). Add ABI regression coverage so exchange mode preserves the null-destination-path fault.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:29:12.677915290Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:32:51.627211232Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T04:32:51.625059999Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-qk9v5","title":"PORT: 16 nis_* prints + group ops + nis_destroy_object","description":"Continue NIS+ libnsl parity. Ship 16 nis_* stubs across print helpers, group ops, and one cleanup helper. Print helpers (9) — each writes a single \"(NIS+ unsupported)\\n\" line to stdout; arguments accepted but ignored: nis_print_directory / nis_print_entry / nis_print_group / nis_print_group_entry / nis_print_link / nis_print_object / nis_print_result / nis_print_rights / nis_print_table. Group ops (6) returning nis_error codes: nis_creategroup / nis_destroygroup / nis_addmember / nis_removemember return NIS_NAMEUNREACHABLE (5); nis_verifygroup returns NIS_NAMEUNREACHABLE; nis_ismember returns 0 (FALSE — bool_t = int) since no group can be queried. Cleanup (1): nis_destroy_object(*obj) is a void no-op since our query stubs never actually allocate objects.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T18:42:29.743917469Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T18:47:07.351889582Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T18:47:07.349839780Z","close_reason":"shipped: 16 NIS+ stubs (9 prints + 6 group ops + void nis_destroy_object) + 7 abi tests covering print-no-crash invariant and NIS_NAMEUNREACHABLE returns","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"bd-qn6q1","title":"PORT: 51 GLIBC_PRIVATE _thread_db_* libthread_db offset/size data symbols","description":"Add 51 GLIBC_PRIVATE _thread_db_* internal data symbols to close the libc.so.6 thread-debug surface gap. These are read-only size_t constants exported by glibc for the libthread_db.so.1 loader (used by gdb attach) to interpret the offsets/sizes within glibcs internal struct pthread layout. We dont own a real struct pthread, so we ship zero-valued placeholders; gdb sees offset=0 everywhere and falls back to \"thread debugging not supported\" rather than crashing the loader (which is the contract for \"we are not glibc\"). Symbols include: const_thread_area; dtv_*; link_map_l_tls_modid/offset; list_t_next/prev; pthread_cancelhandling/dtvp/eventbuf*/key_data*/key_struct*/list/nextevent/report_events/schedparam_sched_priority/schedpolicy/specific/start_routine/tid; rtld_global__dl_*; sizeof_*; td_eventbuf_t_*; td_thr_events_t_*; and the four ___nptl_/__pthread_keys aliases.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T21:46:06.743672542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T21:46:06.743672542Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-qn6q1","title":"PORT: 51 GLIBC_PRIVATE _thread_db_* libthread_db offset/size data symbols","description":"Add 51 GLIBC_PRIVATE _thread_db_* internal data symbols to close the libc.so.6 thread-debug surface gap. These are read-only size_t constants exported by glibc for the libthread_db.so.1 loader (used by gdb attach) to interpret the offsets/sizes within glibcs internal struct pthread layout. We dont own a real struct pthread, so we ship zero-valued placeholders; gdb sees offset=0 everywhere and falls back to \"thread debugging not supported\" rather than crashing the loader (which is the contract for \"we are not glibc\"). Symbols include: const_thread_area; dtv_*; link_map_l_tls_modid/offset; list_t_next/prev; pthread_cancelhandling/dtvp/eventbuf*/key_data*/key_struct*/list/nextevent/report_events/schedparam_sched_priority/schedpolicy/specific/start_routine/tid; rtld_global__dl_*; sizeof_*; td_eventbuf_t_*; td_thr_events_t_*; and the four ___nptl_/__pthread_keys aliases.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T21:46:06.743672542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T21:49:47.120513590Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T21:49:47.118366246Z","close_reason":"shipped: 50 GLIBC_PRIVATE _thread_db_* zeroed placeholders + 7 abi tests; libthread_db introspects no thread layout and gracefully degrades","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-qpj3","title":"syscall: renameat2 invalid flags should override null newpath EFAULT with EINVAL","description":"Host glibc returns EINVAL for renameat2(AT_FDCWD, \".\", AT_FDCWD, NULL, 0x80000000). Add ABI regression coverage proving bad flags dominate a null destination path.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:19:53.609139072Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-21T23:00:59.166757001Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T23:00:59.164534785Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-qq59x","title":"syscall: timer_gettime deleted timer handle with null output should still return EINVAL exactly","description":"Host glibc returns EINVAL for timer_gettime(timer_id, NULL) after timer_delete(timer_id) succeeds, so the deleted-handle contract dominates the null-output path. Add ABI regression coverage for that precedence.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:40:00.250837246Z","created_by":"AmberSignal","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:46:01.235035130Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T04:46:01.231817619Z","close_reason":"timer_gettime(deleted, NULL) → EINVAL pinned (deleted-handle dominates null output).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-qrq1q","title":"PORT: flopen + flopenat (libbsd open-with-advisory-lock)","description":"FreeBSD/libbsd flopen(path, flags, [mode]) atomically opens a file AND acquires an advisory file-level lock (LOCK_EX by default; LOCK_SH if O_SHLOCK is set in flags; LOCK_NB for non-blocking via O_NONBLOCK). Companion flopenat(dirfd, path, flags, [mode]) is the dirfd-relative variant. Used by daemons and daemon-managers (rc.d, supervisord, systemd unit helpers) to enforce single-instance pid files. Returns fd on success, -1 with errno on either open failure or lock failure (after closing the fd on lock failure). Currently missing entirely from frankenlibc-abi. Implementation: thin orchestration shims over the existing open/openat + flock; handle the O_SHLOCK / O_EXLOCK / O_NONBLOCK sentinel-flag bits per BSD spec.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T05:48:33.404856733Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T05:52:30.241612499Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T05:52:30.239542609Z","close_reason":"shipped: unistd_abi flopen+flopenat with O_SHLOCK/O_EXLOCK strip + flock-after-open + close-on-lock-fail; 8 tests; clippy-clean; rch-built","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
